$ Oracle Automatic Storage Management (ASM)
@ ASM

*Oracle Automatic Storage Management* (ASM) is → development/databases/Oracle[Oracle's] alternative to conventional
  • volume managers,
  • → Linux/filesystem/filesystems[file systems] and
  • raw devices
ASM is both, a volume manager *and* a file system.

ASM stores  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/Automatic-Storage-Management/file[(ASM) files] in
  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/Automatic-Storage-Management/disk-group[ASM disk groups].
-
An ASM file belongs to *one* disk group - but a disk group might contain files from different → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database[databases].
-
A database can spread its files on multiple disk groups.

ASM might also uses → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/managed[OMF].

{ Configuring ASM

  ASM can be configured with
    • development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus
    • ASMCMD (the *Oracle ASM Command Line Utility*)
    • ASMCA (the *Oracle ASM Configuration Assistant*)

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/managed
